						<div class="postbody">Seems like many people are interested in making pixel art. The more the better. I'd like to contribute animations too, I can do it to any character at any size, any amount of frames(preferably few, otherwise it would take too long). But anyway the sprites can be non animated nor detailed during the programming. Quick done images, and if the main gameplay gets done, then add detail and frames to the images. So you don't waste talent in something that is not clear if it will be ever finished, until the phisics and moves get done. Look at my only decent finished game(Game Maker): <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://snowmoons.com/downloads.php?cmd=get_file&amp;id=641">http://snowmoons.com/downloads.php?cmd=get_file&amp;id=641</a><!-- m -->
